Conclusion

This study compared three multivariate regression techniques for predicting octane values from IR spectral data. The results demonstrate the usefulness of dimensionality reduction methods such as PCR and PLS when working with highly correlated spectral variables. The model with the lowest RMSE was selected as the most suitable approach for octane prediction.

